[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA heap-buffer-overflow was detected by AddressSanitizer during fuzz testing of the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TestFuzzCryptoCertificateDataSetPEM` harness. The overflow occurs in the function [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` when copying data into a heap-allocated [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer. The issue triggers a write of [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m bytes just past the end of a [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m-byte [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue type: heap-buffer-overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmulti-byte write overflow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow is reported at line [0m[1;36m457[0m[39m of `libfreerdp/crypto/x509_utils.c` inside [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` function.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The malicious write occurs in an `__asan_memcpy` interceptor, indicating a buffer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcopy that exceeds the allocated region.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The faulty allocation is only [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes long, but the code attempts to write [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes into it.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzing harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TestFuzzCryptoCertificateDataSetPEM.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m passes certificate data in PEM format to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe code under test, triggering the overflow.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call stack trace:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `__asan_memcpy` in AddressSanitizer  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`x509_utils.[0m[1;92mc:457[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `freerdp_rsa_from_x509` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`certificate.[0m[1;92mc:1259[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `freerdp_certificate_new_from_x509` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `freerdp_certificate_new_from` [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`certificate.[0m[1;92mc:1341[0m[39m` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `[0m[1;36m1358[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `freerdp_certificate_data_new_from_pem` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`certificate_data.[0m[1;92mc:154[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuzz harness[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant observations:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow boundary is precisely at the end of the allocated buffer [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0x5020000009b0[0m[39m`–`[0m[1;36m0x5020000009b5[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, showing a zero-byte gap before the invalid [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Shadow memory indicates a redzone immediately following the buffer, confirming a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-based overflow.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas to investigate for a comprehensive understanding:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocation logic and size calculation in [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m452[0m[39m in `x509_utils.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- How subject alternative names are parsed and copied—ensure buffer sizes account [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor actual data lengths.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Downstream callers in `certificate.c` and `certificate_data.c` to understand how [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput lengths propagate through certificate parsing routines.[0m                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibfreerdp/crypto/certificate.[0m[1;92mc:1255[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1261[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1255[0m[39m:   [0m[39mBOOL rc = FALSE;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1256[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1257[0m[39m:   [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcert[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1258[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1259[0m[39m:   [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mx509_validate_subject_aternative_names[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcert->x509[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1260[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1261[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Correct buffer allocation and copying in x509_validate_subject_aternative_names:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Replace the current `[0m[1;35mmalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mstrlen[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with allocation based on the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mASN.[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m string length:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Compute `size_t san_len = [0m[1;35mASN1_STRING_length[0m[1;39m([0m[39mgen_name->d.dNSName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Allocate `dns_name = [0m[1;35mmalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39msan_len + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - On allocation failure, set the overall result flag to FALSE and break out [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof the loop.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Copy exactly `san_len` bytes from the ASN.[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m string into `dns_name`:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdns_name, [0m[1;35mASN1_STRING_get0_data[0m[1;39m([0m[39mgen_name->d.dNSName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, san_len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Null-terminate: `dns_name[0m[1;39m[[0m[39msan_len[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m;`[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. After calling `[0m[1;35mverify_san[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdns_name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, free `dns_name` regardless of success [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor failure.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Preserve the result of SAN validation through to the caller:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Introduce a `BOOL result = TRUE;` at the start of the function.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. If `verify_san` fails or memory allocation fails, set `result = FALSE` and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbreak out of the loop.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. At the end of the function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrently `return TRUE;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, change to `return [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresult;` so that any validation or memory failure propagates correctly.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Ensure callers abort on validation failure [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno changes needed there, but after [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis fix they will correctly receive FALSE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `freerdp_rsa_from_x509` already checks the return of [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` and returns FALSE on failure.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No modifications to harness or external code are necessary.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Validation and side-effects:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This patch prevents the heap-buffer-overflow by matching the copy length to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe ASN.[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-declared string length.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Null-termination ensures `verify_san` receives a valid C string.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Propagating the `result` flag maintains existing logic that rejects [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcertificates with invalid SANs.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - On allocation failures, the function now gracefully aborts parsing rather than[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mundefined behavior.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No external dependencies or harness code are modified, preserving the existing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtest and fuzz harness functionality.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A fuzzing run with AddressSanitizer on FreeRDP’s PEM certificate loader [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`TestFuzzCryptoCertificateDataSetPEM`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggers:  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  heap-buffer-overflow at x509_utils.[0m[1;92mc:457[0m[39m in [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mx509_validate_subject_aternative_names[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  WRITE of size [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x5020000009b5[0m[39m thread T0[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m __asan_memcpy[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m x509_validate_subject_aternative_names[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m freerdp_rsa_from_x509[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #… [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocator had provided only [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes for a DNS name, but `memcpy` wrote more [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m20[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, leading to an overflow [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past the region.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace shows the call chain through certificate parsing and fuzz target.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey observations  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The vulnerable code lives in `libfreerdp/crypto/x509_utils.c`, function [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mx509_validate_subject_aternative_names[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst X509* cert[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow arises from allocating `[0m[1;35mstrlen[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m+[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m` bytes—but `strlen` is [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomputed on a non-null‐terminated ASN1 string—and then copying [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mASN1_STRING_length[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` bytes without ensuring the buffer size matches.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m drives the PEM parser but is not [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe root cause.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introduces local variables: `ASN1_OCTET_STRING *ext`, `GENERAL_NAMES *gens`, and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmarks the return value `result`.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Replaces `[0m[1;35mX509_get_ext_d2i[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcert, NID_subject_alt_name, NULL, NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with a call [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto `[0m[1;35mX509_get_ext_d2i[0m[1;39m([0m[39mx509, NID_subject_alt_name, &critical, NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Calls a new helper [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mGENERAL_NAMES_new_from_str[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar*[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mASN1_STRING_get0_data[0m[1;39m([0m[39mext->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, ext->length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto build a `GENERAL_NAMES` structure, then extracts `gens->names` into `san_names`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Iterates SAN entries, allocates `san_len+[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m` bytes, copies the raw data, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnull-terminates, calls `[0m[1;35mverify_san[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdns_name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and updates `result`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Frees the allocated structures appropriately.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch application result  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Compilation errors:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • use of undeclared identifier `x509` in the `X509_get_ext_d2i` call [0m[1;39m([0m[39mshould have[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeen `cert`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • call to undeclared function `GENERAL_NAMES_new_from_str`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • passing an `unsigned char*` to a parameter expecting an `ASN1_STRING*`.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • assigning an `int` return from `GENERAL_NAMES_new_from_str` to `GENERAL_NAMES [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m*`.  [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • accessing `gens->names` fails because `struct stack_st_GENERAL_NAME` is [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincomplete.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • call to undeclared function `verify_san`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for further investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The original `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` implementation in [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`x509_utils.c`, especially allocation and copying of `ASN1_STRING` data.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The definitions and intended use of “GENERAL_NAMES” versus OpenSSL’s [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mSTACK_OF[0m[1;39m([0m[39mGENERAL_NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` abstraction.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The availability and correct prototypes for `GENERAL_NAMES_new_from_str` and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`verify_san` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlikely missing headers or helper modules[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- How SAN extensions are extracted via `X509_get_ext_d2i` and parsed into [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`GENERAL_NAME` stacks in other parts of the codebase.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Overall certificate parsing flow in `freerdp_rsa_from_x509` and [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_certificate_data_new_from_pem` to ensure consistent handling of ASN.[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstrings and memory bounds.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m220[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m221[0m[39m:- the strings array is allocated lazily, when we first have to store a[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m222[0m[39m:  string.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m223[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m224[0m[39m:- allocated contains the size of the strings array, or [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m if[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m225[0m[39m:  allocation failed.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m226[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m227[0m[39m:- count contains the actual count of strings in the strings array.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m228[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m229[0m[39m:- maximum limits the number of strings we can store in the strings[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m230[0m[39m:  array: beyond, the extractor returns [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m to short-cut the search.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m231[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m232:e[0m[39mxtract_string stores in the string list OPENSSL strings,[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m233[0m[39m:that must be freed with OPENSSL_free.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m235[0m[39m:*[0m[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m236[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Initial issue: While fuzzing `TestFuzzCryptoCertificateDataSetPEM`, [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer reported a heap-buffer-overflow in [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` when copying a DNS SAN string.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Patch attempt: The developer removed the original [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` implementation, introduced a helper [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`verify_san` to validate DNS names per RFC-[0m[1;36m1035[0m[39m, and rewrote the SAN validation to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muse `ASN1_STRING_to_UTF8` instead of manual `malloc`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`memcpy`.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Patch result: The modified file failed to compile. Errors arose from stray [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumeric labels [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m431[0m[39m:` and `[0m[1;36m432[0m[39m:`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, an unused expression, and a duplicate [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefinition of `verify_san`.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • ASan report shows a write of size [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m just past an allocated [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m-byte heap region[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names`.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The vulnerable code calls  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     dns_name = [0m[1;35mmalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mstrlen[0m[1;39m([0m[39msource[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdns_name, source, [0m[1;35mASN1_STRING_length[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     without copying the terminating byte correctly, leading to out-of-bounds [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrites.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The crash occurs at the first `memcpy` in [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`x509_validate_subject_aternative_names`, invoked during PEM certificate loading [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand RSA extraction in `freerdp_certificate_new_from_x509`.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The overflow is reported in the SAN validation step [0m[1;39m([0m[39mGEN_DNS type[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Allocation size is `[0m[1;35mstrlen[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m+[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`, but the code uses `ASN1_STRING_length` as[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe copy size, which may mismatch `strlen` or omit the null byte.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • No null-terminator is explicitly set before passing to `verify_san`, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompounding the risk.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch attempt details  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The patch deletes the old function body starting at line [0m[1;36m428[0m[39m and adds:  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – A new static helper `[0m[1;35mverify_san[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst char* name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that checks label [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlengths, allowed characters, and overall length per RFC-[0m[1;36m1035[0m[39m.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – A rewritten `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` that calls [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ASN1_STRING_to_UTF8` to obtain a properly sized UTF-[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`utf8`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, calls [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`verify_san`, and frees `utf8` via `OPENSSL_free`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The patch inserted literal line-number prefixes [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m431[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;36m432[0m[39m:`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m — [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpresumably from an editor diff view — which are not valid C syntax.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The codebase already contains a `verify_san` further down [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m929[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mso the patch’s new `static BOOL verify_san` conflicts with it.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch application log  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Error at `x509_utils.[0m[1;92mc:431:4[0m[39m`: “expected ‘;’ after expression” pointing at [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;36m431[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Warning: “expression result unused” for the same stray label.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Error at `x509_utils.[0m[1;92mc:473:1[0m[39m`: “expected identifier or ‘[0m[1;39m([0m[39m’” pointing at [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;36m432[0m[39m:`.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Error at `x509_utils.[0m[1;92mc:929:6[0m[39m`: “redefinition of ‘verify_san’”, because the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile already defines that helper.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Further areas to investigate  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The existing `verify_san` definition at the bottom of `x509_utils.c`: [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetermine whether it should be reused or consolidated.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The original `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` callers and memory [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanagement patterns, including how SAN strings are allocated, null-terminated, and [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m465[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdns_name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m466[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m471[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35msk_GENERAL_NAME_pop_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39msan_names, GENERAL_NAME_free[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m472[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Remove stray labels and duplicate helper  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Delete the literal “[0m[1;36m431[0m[39m:” and “[0m[1;36m432[0m[39m:” labels that were mistakenly inserted into[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`x509_utils.c`.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove the newly added static `[0m[1;35mverify_san[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst char* name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` implementation [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m431[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m473[0m[39m in the patch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The file already contains a global `BOOL [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mverify_san[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst char *subjectAltName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at ~line [0m[1;36m929[0m[39m; reuse that instead of [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mredefining it.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Forward‐declare the existing helper  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Near the top of `x509_utils.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter the `#include` blocks[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add a prototype:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `extern BOOL [0m[1;35mverify_san[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst char* subjectAltName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This ensures the compiler knows about the existing implementation before it’s [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mused.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Rewrite `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` to use `ASN1_STRING_to_UTF8`  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove the old manual `malloc`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`memcpy` logic and the `char *dns_name` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvariable entirely.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Change the function body to:  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Declare `unsigned char* utf8 = NULL;` and keep `BOOL result = TRUE;`.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Obtain the SAN extension via `X509_get_ext_d2i`; if absent, return TRUE.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Loop over each GENERAL_NAME entry. For `GEN_DNS` types:  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       – Call `[0m[1;35mASN1_STRING_to_UTF8[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&utf8, gen_name->d.dNSName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. If it returns a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnegative value, free the SAN stack and return FALSE.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       – Pass `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mutf8` to the existing `[0m[1;35mverify_san[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` helper. If it returns [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFALSE, free `utf8`, free the SAN stack, and return FALSE.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       – Otherwise, free `utf8` [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing `OPENSSL_free`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and continue.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • After the loop, free the SAN stack and return TRUE.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Propagate validation failures  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure the function returns FALSE on any DNS‐name validation failure rather [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthan always returning TRUE. This correctly aborts parsing when invalid SAN data is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencountered.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Clean up and verify  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm there are no undeclared identifiers or unused variables.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run a rebuild to verify compilation succeeds without errors or warnings.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re‐run the existing fuzzing harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TestFuzzCryptoCertificateDataSetPEM`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirm the heap‐buffer‐overflow no longer occurs and no new issues are introduced.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Using `ASN1_STRING_to_UTF8` guarantees a properly sized, null‐terminated buffer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mper patterns in `extract_string`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Reusing the existing `verify_san` helper avoids duplicate definitions and keeps [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSAN validation logic centralized.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Removing stray labels resolves the compiler errors.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Propagating the FALSE return ensures invalid SAN entries are correctly detected, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maligning function behavior with its intent.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This patch only touches the SAN‐validation routine in `x509_utils.c`, preserving [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother fuzzing harnesses, tests, and utility functions unmodified.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libfuzzer run against FreeRDP’s PEM certificate parser [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mTestFuzzCryptoCertificateDataSetPEM[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggered an AddressSanitizer [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in the function `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin `libfreerdp/crypto/x509_utils.c`. The overflow occurs because a [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m-byte [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy` writes into a buffer that was only allocated for [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes. An attempted [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch merely added an `extern BOOL [0m[1;35mverify_san[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst char* subjectAltName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclaration above `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` but made no logical or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation changes. Reproducing the fuzzer after applying this patch yields the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexact same overflow error at the same source location, indicating the patch did not[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maffect the underlying issue.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer invocation  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `[0m[35m/out/[0m[95mTestFuzzCryptoCertificateDataSetPEM[0m[39m -[0m[33mrss_limit_mb[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m2560[0m[39m -[0m[33mtimeout[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m25[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     leads to an ASan report:  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow on address [0m[1;36m0x5020000009b5[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     WRITE of size [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x5020000009b5[0m[39m thread T0[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[33m...[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[39m in x509_validate_subject_aternative_names [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/FreeRDP/libfreerdp/crypto/[0m[95mx509_utils.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m457:4[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[33m...[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m0x5020000009b5[0m[39m is located [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes after [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m-byte region [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x5020000009b0[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x5020000009b5[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     allocated by thread T0 here:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[39m in x509_validate_subject_aternative_names [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/FreeRDP/libfreerdp/crypto/[0m[95mx509_utils.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m452:15[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The log shows that the buffer of [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes returned by `malloc` at line [0m[1;36m452[0m[39m is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately overrun by a `memcpy` at line [0m[1;36m457[0m[39m copying more data than was reserved.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow happens in `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names`, which is [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalled during X.[0m[1;36m509[0m[39m parsing in `freerdp_rsa_from_x509` → [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_certificate_new_from_x509` → `freerdp_certificate_new_from` → [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_certificate_data_new_from_pem` → fuzz harness.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The corrupt buffer is intended to hold a subjectAltName string but is [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munder-allocated relative to the data being copied.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Diff context [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `libfreerdp/crypto/x509_utils.c` around line [0m[1;36m429[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m429[0m[39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +extern BOOL [0m[1;35mverify_san[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst char* subjectAltName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m430[0m[39m  BOOL [0m[1;35mx509_validate_subject_aternative_names[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst X509* cert[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m431[0m[39m      [0m[1;35mSTACK_OF[0m[1;39m([0m[39mGENERAL_NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m *san_names = NULL;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m432[0m[39m      int i, count;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other edits were made. The patch simply introduces an external declaration [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor a `verify_san` function but does not change the allocation size or the copy [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic in `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names`.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Running the fuzzer again produces an identical ASan heap-buffer-overflow at [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`x509_utils.[0m[1;92mc:457[0m[39m` with the same stack trace and memory layout, demonstrating that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe patch had no effect on the overflow.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Further Investigation  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   To obtain a holistic view of this vulnerability, the following areas in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase should be reviewed:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The implementation of `x509_validate_subject_aternative_names` in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`libfreerdp/crypto/x509_utils.c`, especially:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • How the length of the subjectAltName string is determined.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • How much memory is allocated via `malloc` at line [0m[1;36m452[0m[39m.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The parameters passed to `memcpy` at line [0m[1;36m457[0m[39m.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any helper or verification functions intended to sanitize or validate SAN [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentries [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., the undeclared `verify_san`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, to see if they ought to guard or [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtruncate inputs before copying.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The call chain from `freerdp_certificate_data_new_from_pem` → [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_certificate_new_from` → `freerdp_certificate_new_from_x509` → [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`freerdp_rsa_from_x509` to understand how X.[0m[1;36m509[0m[39m fields are parsed and passed down [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto the SAN-validation routine.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Allocation and bounds-checking conventions elsewhere in X.[0m[1;36m509[0m[39m utilities to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure consistent defensive programming when handling untrusted input.[0m              [2m                [0m
